                <DIV class="ReviewHeading">Amazon.com:</DIV>
                <span id="Label1">The authors of <I>Wine for Dummies</I> and <I>White Wine for Dummies</I> have produced a handy primer on the fundamentals of red wine.  After a brief introduction to the varieties of grapes and the seven classic types of red wine, the reader (and taster!) is introduced to the world's greatest offerings, including less recognized wines from Chile and Australia.  The familiar Dummies-style "Part of Tens" includes 10 wine-tasting exercises using affordable vintages.</span>
              
</td></tr></table>
